Probabilistic Methods, Rule Learning. 

Probabilistic Methods: The paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques for knowledge acquisition in complex engineering domains. It suggests that combining the strengths of several complementing learning techniques can help overcome the weaknesses of individual techniques. This approach involves probabilistic methods, which are used to model uncertainty and make predictions based on probability distributions.

Rule Learning: The paper discusses the macro and micro perspectives of multistrategy learning. The macro perspective involves decomposing a complex learning task into well-defined learning tasks, while the micro perspective involves designing multistrategy learning techniques for each task. Rule learning is one of the techniques that can be used in the micro perspective to support the acquisition of knowledge for each task.
